* 1116_data_overlap.sno — DATA field name reuse: two types share an accessor name
* Rung 11. 3 assertions.
* When a field name is reused across DATA types, the accessor dispatches
* by the runtime type of its argument.

        data('node(val,lson,rson)')
        data('clunk(value,lson)')

*       node's rson accessor still works after clunk defines lson
        a = node('x', 'y', 'z')
        b = node()
        lson(b) = a
        differ(rson(lson(b)), 'z')                   :f(e001)
        output = 'FAIL 1116/001: node.rson after clunk data def' :(end)
e001

*       value() (the built-in) still retrieves variable by name
        differ(value('b'), b)                   :f(e002)
        output = 'FAIL 1116/002: value() still works after clunk' :(end)
e002

*       clunk's own lson accessor works on a clunk instance
        c = clunk('alpha', 'beta')
        differ(lson(c), 'beta')                   :f(e003)
        output = 'FAIL 1116/003: clunk.lson accessor'  :(end)
e003

        output = 'PASS 1116_data_overlap (3/3)'
end
